-- Alrosa Names Former Russian Railways’ Ryaschin First Deputy CEO
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2012-06-19T08:37:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-19/alrosa-names-former-russian-railways-ryaschin-first-deputy-ceo.html
OAO Alrosa,  Russia ’s state-run
diamond miner, named former OAO Russian Railways executive Ilya Ryaschin as first deputy chief executive officer.  Andrey Polyakov, an Alrosa spokesman, confirmed the hiring
by phone. Ryaschin was previously head of the budget planning
department of Russian Railways, a state-controlled company where
Alrosa CEO Fyodor Andreev worked as a vice-president until 2009.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
